The United Nations Wednesday named  Norwegian Terje Roed Larsen as special coordinator for the Israeli occupied  territories.
UN Secretary General Boutros Boutros-Ghali said that Roed Larsen, 47,  would take up the post on June 1.
He said that Norway, Israel and the Palestine Liberation Organization had  all agreed to the nomination which he said would be a very important one for  the Middle East peace process.
Roed Larsen is currently adviser on the Middle East at the Norwegian  foreign ministry.
He will be responsible for coordinating international efforts to develop  the economic base of the territories in the wake of the Israeli-PLO peace  accord.
